The '''Secretaria Nacional de Ciencia y Tecnologia''' (National Secretariat of Science and Technology, SENACYT), is the [[government of Ecuador|government]] technical body responsible for implementing policies for science, [[technology]], and [[innovation]] in [[Ecuador]].<ref name="scidev.net">{{cite news|url=http://www.scidev.net/es/agriculture-and-environment/finance/news/nuevos-cambios-en-la-ciencia-de-ecuador.html|title=Nuevos cambios en la ciencia de Ecuador|publisher=Scidev.net|language=Spanish|accessdate=2009-05-11}}</ref>

SENACYT is an [[autonomous agent|autonomous agency]] of the Ministry of Planning and National Development. SENACYT works alongside [[university|universities]] and the [[private sector]] to promote [[applied research]]. The major focus of its research has been in [[agriculture]] and [[environmental impact]] on [[raw material]] extraction.

The National Secretary of Science and Technology is Dr. Ruben Berrocal; he was sworn in on July 10, 2008. <ref name="Ecuador">{{cite web|url=http://www.presidencia.gov.ec/articulom.php?ar_codigo=230&ca_codigo=53&ca_padre=0 |title=Secretaría Nacional de Ciencia y Tecnología |publisher=República del Ecuador |language=Spanish |accessdate=2009-05-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090319233351/http://www.presidencia.gov.ec/articulom.php?ar_codigo=230&ca_codigo=53&ca_padre=0 |archivedate=March 19, 2009 }}</ref>

